title: Ramen Rock: Cult Band Shonen Knife Sings about Food, Not Love
itunes:title: Ramen Rock: Cult Band Shonen Knife Sings about Food, Not Love
itunes:subtitle: This week, NPR's Maria Godoy reports on pop-punk band Shonen Knife; Milk Street travels to Taipei, to a cooking school that teaches street food; our recipe for shaved zucchini salad; and dry versus sweet wines. Originally aired August 24, 2017.
description:
This week, NPR’s Maria Godoy reports on pop-punk band Shonen Knife; Milk Street travels to Taipei, to a cooking school that teaches street food; our recipe for shaved zucchini salad; and dry versus sweet wines. Originally aired August 24, 2017.

Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information.
